The paper presents a novel neural network model for joint POS tagging and dependency parsing, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model uses bidirectional LSTMs to learn feature representations, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that the model handles the feature-engineering problem, which is a common challenge in NLP and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The model's performance is evaluated on 19 languages, which suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories, which often involve multi-lingual or cross-lingual analysis.
